00:44:55,440 --> 00:44:57,910
Is there something you're looking for?

556
00:44:58,810 --> 00:45:00,380
Oh, no.

557
00:45:01,040 --> 00:45:02,940
I was just browsing.

558
00:45:02,940 --> 00:45:04,010
Right.

559
00:45:21,860 --> 00:45:24,230
<i>When did it all go wrong?</i>

560
00:45:34,140 --> 00:45:36,480
<i>What am I so afraid of?</i>

561
00:45:45,890 --> 00:45:47,090
<i>Father.</i>

562
00:45:49,260 --> 00:45:51,130
<i>I think</i>

563
00:45:52,790 --> 00:45:54,230
<i>I was most afraid</i>

564
00:45:55,100 --> 00:45:57,530
<i>of having to tell you</i>

565
00:45:59,070 --> 00:46:02,240
<i>this one day.</i>

566
00:46:12,280 --> 00:46:13,780
<i>Father,</i>

567
00:46:14,820 --> 00:46:17,250
<i>for over forty years' time,</i>

568
00:46:21,590 --> 00:46:23,890
<i>I didn't become anything.</i>

569
00:46:33,700 --> 00:46:34,840
<i>And</i>

570
00:46:35,700 --> 00:46:39,370
<i>during that time of
not becoming anything,</i>

571
00:46:41,580 --> 00:46:44,110
<i>I think I've disappeared somewhere.</i>

572
00:46:52,920 --> 00:46:55,290
<i>I don't want to tell you what happened</i>

573
00:46:57,960 --> 00:46:59,590
<i>in detail.</i>

574
00:47:03,630 --> 00:47:05,900
<i>Actually, I can't tell you.</i>

575
00:47:10,340 --> 00:47:11,940
<i>Because, to be honest,</i>

576
00:47:13,240 --> 00:47:16,040
<i>I'm not even sure what made me</i>

577
00:47:18,010 --> 00:47:19,810
<i>like this.</i>

578
00:47:22,120 --> 00:47:23,250
<i>She's not the baby mama.</i>

579
00:47:23,650 --> 00:47:24,930
<i>Then who is she?</i>

580
00:47:25,590 --> 00:47:27,420
<i>She's a woman I know.</i>

581
00:47:29,190 --> 00:47:30,390
<i>We might die together.</i>

582
00:47:36,970 --> 00:47:38,930
<i>If someone were to hear what it was,</i>

583
00:47:40,640 --> 00:47:43,540
<i>they might get angry or sneer at me</i>

584
00:47:45,210 --> 00:47:47,510
<i>for thinking of dying
because of a petty issue.</i>

585
00:47:50,710 --> 00:47:52,980
<i>That kind of small and common thing</i>

586
00:47:52,980 --> 00:47:55,220
<i>happened to me, too.</i>

587
00:47:58,390 --> 00:48:00,990
<i>It's not a great reason</i>

588
00:48:04,830 --> 00:48:07,130
<i>that everyone would nod their heads to.</i>

589
00:48:09,530 --> 00:48:10,930
<i>I'm sorry about that.</i>

590
00:48:10,930 --> 00:48:13,170
<i>(I appreciate what you did that day.)</i>

591
00:48:21,380 --> 00:48:23,280
<i>I couldn't save myself.</i>

592
00:48:24,980 --> 00:48:26,950
<i>I couldn't protect myself.</i>

593
00:48:31,250 --> 00:48:32,450
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

594
00:48:57,080 --> 00:48:59,450
<i>(Last Unit)</i>

595
00:48:59,450 --> 00:49:00,510
<i>Actually,</i>

596
00:49:01,150 --> 00:49:03,520
<i>my job allows people</i>

597
00:49:03,990 --> 00:49:07,560
<i>to call me any time for anything.</i>

598
00:49:10,390 --> 00:49:11,190
<i>If you are</i>

599
00:49:11,760 --> 00:49:13,660
<i>in a situation where you need someone,</i>

600
00:49:14,460 --> 00:49:15,760
<i>please contact me.</i>

601
00:49:38,290 --> 00:49:39,620
I thought

602
00:49:39,750 --> 00:49:42,520
it was strange
she didn't give me a book.

603
00:49:44,060 --> 00:49:46,330
I called the publishing house earlier

604
00:49:46,530 --> 00:49:47,830
but I couldn't believe them.

605
00:49:50,300 --> 00:49:51,670
Are you okay?

606
00:49:52,830 --> 00:49:53,670
Huh?

607
00:49:53,940 --> 00:49:55,000
Oh, yes.

608
00:49:56,370 --> 00:49:58,310
She must have her reasons.

609
00:50:01,040 --> 00:50:04,550
Nowadays, you can't fire someone easily.

610
00:50:04,950 --> 00:50:06,350
So if you endure,

611
00:50:06,810 --> 00:50:08,480
then things work out.

612
00:50:08,480 --> 00:50:10,320
But she quit again.

613
00:50:13,650 --> 00:50:16,320
Is it true that Bu-jeong quit?

614
00:50:16,890 --> 00:50:17,890
Yes.

615
00:50:19,360 --> 00:50:20,800
A few months ago,

616
00:50:21,200 --> 00:50:23,800
she resigned out of the blue.

617
00:50:25,200 --> 00:50:26,330
She has such a temper.

618
00:50:26,800 --> 00:50:29,940
She's over forty.
She should know how to endure.

619
00:50:31,910 --> 00:50:33,670
Then that's fine.

620
00:50:36,480 --> 00:50:38,480
What's fine?

621
00:50:38,610 --> 00:50:39,850
Chang-suk.

622
00:50:40,010 --> 00:50:42,950
It's difficult for even
young people to get a job.

623
00:50:43,520 --> 00:50:44,890
If she didn't hear

624
00:50:45,390 --> 00:50:48,720
her superiors say, "Leave" or "Quit,"

625
00:50:48,720 --> 00:50:50,320
then that's fine.

626
00:50:55,100 --> 00:50:56,960
Since she was 19,

627
00:50:56,960 --> 00:50:59,000
she worked at a part-time job.

628
00:50:59,000 --> 00:51:02,500
She worked without rest
for over 20 years.

629
00:51:03,340 --> 00:51:05,570
She should now rest.

630
00:51:06,240 --> 00:51:07,240
I'm just

631
00:51:08,280 --> 00:51:10,140
sorry toward Jeong-su.

632
00:51:10,540 --> 00:51:12,680
I don't know what to say to him.

633
00:51:13,480 --> 00:51:15,020
Right.

634
00:51:18,590 --> 00:51:20,450
- Min-ja.
- Yes?

635
00:51:21,420 --> 00:51:23,860
For now, don't tell Bu-jeong...

636
00:51:25,930 --> 00:51:27,930
I can't say anything outright.

637
00:51:28,160 --> 00:51:29,900
She'll hurl insults at me.

638
00:51:30,030 --> 00:51:32,070
You don't know

639
00:51:32,370 --> 00:51:34,470
how nasty she can be.

640
00:51:35,540 --> 00:51:36,400
Right.

641
00:51:37,970 --> 00:51:39,040
I'm sorry.

642
00:51:39,910 --> 00:51:41,240
And I'm grateful.

643
00:51:43,710 --> 00:51:46,480
How is your health?

644
00:51:47,550 --> 00:51:49,150
Oh, well,

645
00:51:49,780 --> 00:51:52,320
it gets better, then it gets worse.

646
00:51:58,790 --> 00:52:01,560
Take one. You'll get an energy boost.

647
00:52:01,830 --> 00:52:02,860
It's new.

648
00:52:02,860 --> 00:52:05,370
It's okay. You take it.

649
00:52:05,830 --> 00:52:07,600
I'll be going now.

650
00:52:07,700 --> 00:52:08,770
Oh, dear.

651
00:52:33,590 --> 00:52:37,600
<i>Lee Bu-jeong: If you're free tonight,</i>

652
00:52:37,600 --> 00:52:39,500
<i>I'd like to book you.</i>

653
00:53:06,290 --> 00:53:10,890
<i>(7 PM... Should I...)</i>

654
00:53:14,100 --> 00:53:20,400
<i>(7 PM... Should I get a room at
a motel near the studio apartment?)</i>

655
00:54:18,500 --> 00:54:20,030
<i>That's fine.</i>

656
00:54:57,510 --> 00:54:59,310
You should sell products you know.

657
00:54:59,310 --> 00:55:01,380
How can you sell something
you don't know?

658
00:55:01,580 --> 00:55:02,780
Aren't I right?

659
00:55:04,150 --> 00:55:07,410
It hasn't been long
since she was assigned here.

660
00:55:07,410 --> 00:55:08,820
I'm sorry.

661
00:55:09,650 --> 00:55:12,020
While you continue to shop,

662
00:55:12,020 --> 00:55:14,690
please contact me if there
are any inconveniences.

663
00:55:14,690 --> 00:55:16,220
I'll always help out.

664
00:55:18,860 --> 00:55:19,960
Goodbye, ma'am.

665
00:55:56,190 --> 00:55:59,970
<i>(Wife: I might be late tonight.)</i>

666
00:55:59,970 --> 00:56:03,370
<i>(If it's too late,
I'll spend the night at Dad's.)</i>

667
00:56:15,320 --> 00:56:17,320
What's gotten you all serious?

668
00:56:18,950 --> 00:56:20,390
Oh, my wife

669
00:56:20,390 --> 00:56:21,990
